## STEP 1 — You Type Command

```
java MusicPlayer
      ↓
OS receives command
```

---

## STEP 2 — OS Creates Process

```
OS
 ↓
Creates JVM Process
 ↓
Assigns PID (example: 1234)
 ↓
Allocates RAM for JVM
```

---

## STEP 3 — JVM Sets Up Memory

```
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│        JVM MEMORY           │
│                             │
│  ┌─────────────────────┐   │
│  │     METHOD AREA     │   │
│  │   (empty for now)   │   │
│  └─────────────────────┘   │
│                             │
│  ┌─────────────────────┐   │
│  │       HEAP          │   │
│  │   (empty for now)   │   │
│  └─────────────────────┘   │
│                             │
│  ┌─────────────────────┐   │
│  │    MAIN THREAD      │   │
│  │      STACK          │   │
│  │   (empty for now)   │   │
│  └─────────────────────┘   │
└─────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## STEP 4 — ClassLoader Loads Class

```
JVM ClassLoader
 ↓
Finds MusicPlayer.class
 ↓
Loads into METHOD AREA

┌─────────────────────────┐
│      METHOD AREA        │
│                         │
│  MusicPlayer.class ✅   │
│  → playSong()           │
│  → downloadSong()       │
│  → likeSong()           │
│  → main()               │
└─────────────────────────┘
```

---

## STEP 5 — JVM Creates Main Thread

```
JVM
 ↓
Creates "main" thread
 ↓
Creates 5 background threads (auto)

┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│           ALL THREADS                │
│                                      │
│  main thread          ← YOUR code   │
│  Reference Handler    ← JVM work    │
│  Finalizer            ← JVM work    │
│  Signal Dispatcher    ← JVM work    │
│  Attach Listener      ← JVM work    │
│  Common Cleaner       ← JVM work    │
└──────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## STEP 6 — main() Called

```
main thread
 ↓
Calls main() method
 ↓
Stack frame pushed

┌─────────────────────┐
│   MAIN THREAD STACK │
│  ┌───────────────┐  │
│  │   main()      │  │  ← TOP
│  └───────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────┘
```

---

## STEP 7 — Object Created in Heap

```
main() executes:
new MusicPlayer()
 ↓
JVM allocates object in HEAP

┌─────────────────────────┐
│         HEAP            │
│  ┌───────────────────┐  │
│  │  MusicPlayer obj  │  │
│  │  address: 0x1A2B  │  │
│  └───────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────┘

Stack holds reference → 0x1A2B
```

---

## STEP 8 — Threads Created

```
main() executes:
new Thread(t1)  → NEW state
new Thread(t2)  → NEW state
new Thread(t3)  → NEW state

┌──────────────────────────────────┐
│  t1 PlayThread     → NEW  ⭕     │
│  t2 DownloadThread → NEW  ⭕     │
│  t3 LikeThread     → NEW  ⭕     │
└──────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## STEP 9 — Threads Started

```
t1.start() → PlayThread     RUNNABLE → RUNNING
t2.start() → DownloadThread RUNNABLE → RUNNING
t3.start() → LikeThread     RUNNABLE → RUNNING

Each thread gets its OWN stack!

┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐
│PlayThread│ │Download  │ │LikeThread│
│  Stack   │ │  Stack   │ │  Stack   │
│playSong()│ │download()│ │likeSong()│
└──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────┘
      ↓             ↓           ↓
  sleeping 5s   sleeping 8s  sleeping 2s
```

---

## STEP 10 — Methods Execute in Parallel

```
Time →  0s       2s       5s              8s
        │        │        │               │
Play    ├────────┼────────┤ ✅ done        │
Download├────────┼────────┼───────────────┤ ✅ done
Like    ├────┤ ✅ done    │               │

Total = 8 seconds only!
```

---

## STEP 11 — Threads Finish

```
Each thread finishes
 ↓
Stack frame popped
 ↓
Thread state → TERMINATED
 ↓
Stack memory released
```

---

## STEP 12 — Program Ends

```
All threads done
 ↓
main thread finishes
 ↓
JVM shuts down
 ↓
OS releases memory
 ↓
Process removed from RAM
```

---

## 🗒️ One Page Summary

```
java MusicPlayer
      ↓
OS creates JVM Process (PID)
      ↓
JVM sets up Heap + Method Area + Stack
      ↓
ClassLoader loads MusicPlayer.class → Method Area
      ↓
JVM creates main thread + 5 background threads
      ↓
main() pushed to Stack
      ↓
new MusicPlayer() → object created in Heap
      ↓
t1, t2, t3 created → NEW state
      ↓
t1.start(), t2.start(), t3.start()
      ↓
Each thread gets own Stack
Each thread runs its method
All run SIMULTANEOUSLY
      ↓
Threads finish → TERMINATED → Stack cleared
      ↓
main finishes → JVM shuts down → RAM freed
```

