## 🔑 Key Points to Remember

```
1. ONE process created  → JVM process
2. SIX threads minimum → 1 main + 5 JVM background
3. ONE heap            → shared by all threads
4. ONE stack per thread → each thread has its own
5. Method Area         → stores class definitions
6. ClassLoader         → loads .class into Method Area
7. new keyword         → creates object in Heap
8. thread.start()      → creates new stack for thread
9. thread.join()       → main waits for thread to finish
10. All threads done   → JVM shuts down → RAM freed
```

